--------------------------------------------------------------------------
File & Directory Commands
Command	Purpose
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

pwd	Show current directory
ls	List files
ls -l	Detailed listing
ls -a	Show hidden files
cd	Change directory
mkdir	Create directory
rmdir	Remove empty directory
rm	Remove files/directories
cp	Copy files
mv	Move/rename files
touch	Create empty file
cat	Display file contents
less	View file page by page
more	View file
head	First lines of file
tail	Last lines of file
tail -f	Follow log file
find	Search files
locate	Fast file search
which	Find command path
whereis	Locate binaries/source/man pages
file	Identify file type
stat	File details
tree	Directory structure
du	Directory size
df -h	Disk usage
basename	Extract filename
dirname	Extract directory path


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Permission Values
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Permission	Value
Read (r)	4
Write (w)	2
Execute (x)	1

Examples:

Mode	Meaning
777	Full access
755	Owner full, others read/execute
644	Owner read/write, others read
600	Owner only

chmod 755 script.sh
chmod +x script.sh
chmod -R 755 directory

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
change ownership and group
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
chown user file
chown user:group file
sudo chgrp -R new_group_name /path/to/directory


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Add existing user to anther group and remove user from the group
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
usermod -aG groupName user
gpasswd -d user groupName


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
add user and delete user
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
adduser username
deluser username
passwd -> for change password
su -> switch user
last -> login log
id -> show id of user


usermod -L usernamem -> lock user account
usermod -U userName  -> unlock user accont

